{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778260820,"nonce":"LKujTtCoHEw7+m9GyT2soWPpT2s=","title":"Δv evaluation pipeline reuses 0.5 m centre-out trials despite 15 cm canonical reach claim","message":"Stage 1 in the proposed regulator-coupling / decoupling-chain programme (exploration, not committed).\n\n**Question.** Are the analytical Δv (+10.8% on rlrmp regime, +1.0% on C\u0026S regime) and the empirical trained-controller Δv (−25% group mean) even computed on the same task?\n\n**Bug.** `_build_canonical_reach_trial_specs` currently reuses the 0.5 m centre-out validation trials despite the function name and run.json claiming a 15 cm canonical reach. This means empirical Δv is measured on a reach that is 3.3× longer than the analytical operating point, confounding every empirical/analytical comparison in synthesis.md §5.3 and §7.1.1.\n\n**Approach.**\n1. Locate and audit `_build_canonical_reach_trial_specs` (src/rlrmp/analysis/ or training scripts). Confirm the mismatch.\n2. Fix the function to honour the canonical 15 cm forward reach (init=(0,0), target=(0.15,0)) as stated in run.json.\n3. Add a regression test asserting `trial_specs.init.pos == (0,0)` and `trial_specs.target.pos == (0.15,0)` after the build step.\n4. Re-evaluate all empirical Δv numbers that appear in synthesis.md §5.3 and §7.1.1 under the corrected geometry.\n5. Re-evaluate the trained controllers on the corrected geometry; update synthesis.md with the corrected numbers.\n\n**Falsification / success criterion.** After geometry+schedule alignment, if the trained Δv shifts from −25% to the +5–15% range (near the analytical prediction), the decoupling hypothesis is largely not needed — the gap was an evaluation artefact. If it stays at −20%, the gap is real and stages 2–9 are warranted.\n\n**Cross-refs.** synthesis.md §5.3, §7.1.1 (bimodal replicate analysis). Codex finding (decoupling-chain plan §1). Training-methods coord c99ad9d.","files":null}]}